## Traps

(Previous session traps still apply.)

- LogRecord reserves these attribute names — never use as `extra` keys:
  msg, message, module, filename, pathname, levelname, levelno, lineno,
  funcName, created, msecs, relativeCreated, thread, threadName,
  processName, process, asctime, name, args, exc_info, exc_text,
  stack_info. Always prefix: column_name, migration_name, etc.

- TrustPosture old names (FULL_AUTONOMY, BLOCKED, ASSISTED,
  HUMAN_DECIDES) are NOT in the backward-compat alias table. Only
  DELEGATED / CONTINUOUS_INSIGHT / SHARED_PLANNING / PSEUDO_AGENT
  are aliased. Use canonical names in new code.

